<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-05T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-05T22:00:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–647: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tihwa</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Paxton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tihwa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-06T09:00:00+06:00">October 6,
                                1947—9 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 7—4:51 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>57. Yesterday informed by Garrison Commander Sung that delayed news recently
                        received by courier from Osman, in absence of radio communications, that
                        Chenghua (remytel to Nanking 367, repeated Washington 49, September 23) fell
                        to his forces about September 21. Opposing leaders have fled leaving all
                        important places in Ashan zone under Osman’s control.</p>
                    <p>Sung maintains that no Chinese regular troops have been engaged in this
                        fighting, [garbled group] cavalry (see page 7 of memo enclosed Tihwa
                        despatch to Department 20, June 30<note n="42" xml:id="d486fn1">Not
                            printed.</note>) remaining at Peitashan.</p>
                    <p>Sent Nanking 379, repeated Department.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paxton</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>